wmsysmon (dockapp to monitor CPU, RAM, swap, uptime, and more)

wmsysmon is a program designed for use with the Window Maker window
manager for the X Window System. It monitors the following system
information: Memory usage, swap usage, I/O throughput, system uptime,
hardware interrupts, paging and swap activity.

There is no man page. Run "wmsysmon --help" for usage.

Note: in the unlikely event that you're using a non-SMP (single core,
single CPU) system, the package will be built differently. If you
build on an SMP machine and install the package on a non-SMP one
(or vice versa), wmsysmon may not work correctly. You can force SMP
support to be enabled or disabled with SMP=yes or SMP=no. The default
is to autodetect, which is what you want if you're going to install
the package on the machine you built it on.
